Doan Ngoc Bao is an Intern AI Engineer with 1 month of commercial internship experience, specializing in AI Agent development, Deep Learning, and Machine Learning. Their core expertise encompasses Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computer Vision, with practical application of Retrieval Augmented Generation (RAG) systems, Large Language Models (LLM) integration, and Sequence to Sequence architectures. Doan has hands-on experience with Transformer models, including fine-tuning ViT5 for Grammatical Error Correction (GEC) and implementing real-time Object Detection using YOLOv11n with Ultralytics. During their internship, they developed a customer service AI agent, integrating data crawling, SQLite, RAG, and Groq API. Their project portfolio further highlights capabilities in data annotation with Roboflow, OCR for text extraction, and building conversational AI agents leveraging LangChain for chat history management.
Technically, Doan is proficient in Python, with foundational knowledge in C and Java. Their robust technical stack includes PyTorch, TensorFlow, Ultralytics, LangChain, Gradio, Pandas, Numpy, Matplotlib, Seaborn, OpenCV, and specialized tools like crawl4ai and Torch. They are adept with SQLite databases and leverage development environments and platforms such as Visual Studio Code, Jupyter Notebook, Linux, Google Colab, GitHub, GIT, Hugging Face, and Roboflow. Doan's domain knowledge extends to real-time systems, data annotation, and the practical implementation of AI agents for customer service and specific tasks like parking detection and receipt OCR. Academically, they are pursuing a Bachelor's in Computer Science with a GPA of 3.3/4.0 and possess an IELTS 6.0+ certification.